<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1"?>

<mixer template="gw.tmpl">
<mixertitle>How to cite <mixer var="GAP"/></mixertitle>

<p>
  If you have used <mixer var="GAP4"/> in the preparation of a paper
  please cite it as described below (in case you still use
  <mixer var="GAP3"/> please see how to
  <a href="/Gap3/cite3.html">cite&nbsp;<mixer var="GAP3"/></a>).
</p>
<dl>
<dt>
[GAP<mixer var="relyear"/>]
</dt>
<dd>
  The <mixer var="GAP"/> Group, <mixer var="GAP"/> -- Groups, Algorithms,
  and Programming, Version 4<mixer var="rel4long"/>.<mixer var="fix4level"/>; 
  <mixer var="relyear"/>.
  (https://www.gap-system.org)
</dd>
</dl>

<p>
  If you have (predominantly) used one or more particular <mixer var="GAP"/>
  packages, please  cite these packages in addition to <mixer var="GAP"/>
  itself. (Either check the package documentation if it suggests how to cite
  it, or use a scheme like:
</p>
<dl>
<dt>
[PKG]
</dt>
<dd>
  &lt;Author name(s)>, &lt;package name> - a <mixer var="GAP"/> package,
  &lt;package version>, &lt;package date>, &lt;package web address>
</dd>
</dl>
<p>
You find the necessary information for each package from the <a
href="/Packages/packages.html">package overview</a> page.)
</p>

<p>
  If you are using BibTeX, you can use the following BibTeX entry for the
  current <mixer var="GAP"/> version:
</p>

<pre>
  @manual{GAP4,
    key          = "GAP",
    organization = "The GAP~Group",
    title        = "{GAP -- Groups, Algorithms, and Programming,
                    Version 4<mixer var="rel4long"/>.<mixer
                    var="fix4level"/>}",
    year         = <mixer var="relyear"/>,
    url          = "\verb+(https://www.gap-system.org)+",
    }
</pre>

<p>
  If you are not using BibTeX, here is the bibliography entry produced
  by BibTeX (in bibliography style `alpha'). You can use this inside
  the bibliography environment of LaTeX.
</p>

<pre>
  \bibitem[GAP]{GAP4}
  The GAP~Group, \emph{GAP -- Groups, Algorithms, and Programming, 
  Version 4<mixer var="rel4long"/>.<mixer var="fix4level"/>}; 
  <mixer var="relyear"/>,
  \verb+(https://www.gap-system.org)+.
</pre>

<p>
  When linking to <mixer var="GAP"/> from a web page you can use the link 
</p>
<pre>
  &lt;a&nbsp;href="https://www.gap-system.org/"&gt;GAP&lt;/a&gt;.
</pre>

<p>
Instructions on citing <mixer var="GAP"/> and its packages may be also found
in the CITATION file in the <mixer var="GAP"/> root directory or displayed
in <mixer var="GAP"/> using the function <mixer manual="Reference: Cite">Cite</mixer>.
</p>

<p>
  We also would be indebted if you inform us about your papers citing 
  <mixer var="GAP"/> by sending a short note to 
  <a href="mailto:support@gap-system.org"><code>support@gap-system.org</code></a>.
</p>

</mixer>

